                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the east wall of the central shrine in the ruined Ādivarāha Perumāḷ temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Pratāpa-Dēvarāya-mahārāya. 1445 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription dated in Krōdhin, Āḍi 20, records the making over of Pāṇaṉ of Śeñji-paṟṟu as a <hi rend="italic">tiruviḷakkukkuḍi</hi> to god Paṉṟi Āḻvār of Śiṅgapuram. </p>						
                            
                        </summary>
